<div>
  <div class="form-group">
    <label>Dungeon Alchemist Export Folder</label>
    <div class="form-fields">
      <input type="text" name="folder" placeholder="Path to exported folder..." readonly />
      <input type="hidden" name="source" value="data" />
      <button type="button" data-action="browse">
        <i class="fas fa-folder-open"></i> Browse
      </button>
    </div>
    <p class="hint">Select the folder exported by Dungeon Alchemist containing the level media (image or video) and JSON.</p>
  </div>

  <nav class="da-tabs" role="tablist">
    <button type="button" class="da-tab-btn da-tab-btn--active" data-tab="scene" role="tab" aria-selected="true">Scene Defaults</button>
    <button type="button" class="da-tab-btn" data-tab="doors" role="tab" aria-selected="false">Doors</button>
    <button type="button" class="da-tab-btn" data-tab="levels" role="tab" aria-selected="false">Levels</button>
  </nav>

  <div class="da-tab-panel" data-tab="scene" role="tabpanel">

    <div class="da-field-card">
      <div class="form-group da-inline-group">
        <label>Background Color</label>
        <div class="form-fields">
          <input type="color" name="backgroundColor" value="#000000" />
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="hint">Scene background color applied to all levels.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="da-field-card">
      <div class="form-group da-inline-group">
        <label>Grid Opacity</label>
        <div class="form-fields">
          <input type="range" name="gridAlpha" min="0" max="1" step="0.05" value="0" />
          <span class="range-value">0.00</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="hint">Opacity of the grid overlay (0 = invisible, 1 = fully visible).</p>
    </div>

    <hr class="da-section-divider" />

    <div class="da-field-card">
      <div class="form-group da-inline-group da-toggle-group">
        <label for="copyImages">Copy Media to World</label>
        <div class="form-fields">
          <label class="da-toggle">
            <input type="checkbox" id="copyImages" name="copyImages" />
            <span class="da-toggle-track">
              <span class="da-toggle-thumb"></span>
            </span>
          </label>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="hint">
        When enabled, copies all floor media into
        <code>worlds/&lt;world&gt;/da-imported/&lt;map-name&gt;/</code>
        and points the scene to the copies.
        Files are renamed to kebab-case.
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>

  <div class="da-tab-panel da-tab-panel--hidden" data-tab="doors" role="tabpanel">

    <div class="da-field-card">
      <div class="form-group da-inline-group">
        <label>Door Texture</label>
        <div class="form-fields da-door-row">
          <select name="doorTexture">
            <option value="">None</option>
            <option value="canvas/doors/small/Door_Metal_Gray_E1_1x1.webp">Metal Gray E1</option>
            <option value="canvas/doors/small/Door_Metal_Rusty_D_1x1.webp">Metal Rusty D</option>
            <option value="canvas/doors/small/Door_Metal_Rusty_F_1x1.webp">Metal Rusty F</option>
            <option value="canvas/doors/small/Door_Stone_Earthy_A_1x1.webp">Stone Earthy A</option>
            <option value="canvas/doors/small/Door_Stone_Earthy_B1_1x1.webp">Stone Earthy B1</option>
            <option value="canvas/doors/small/Door_Stone_Redrock_A_Rusty_1x1.webp">Stone Redrock A (Rusty)</option>
            <option value="canvas/doors/small/Door_Stone_Redrock_B1_1x1.webp">Stone Redrock B1</option>
            <option value="canvas/doors/small/Door_Stone_Volcanic_A_1x1.webp">Stone Volcanic A</option>
            <option value="canvas/doors/small/Door_Stone_Volcanic_B1_1x1.webp">Stone Volcanic B1</option>
            <option value="canvas/doors/small/Door_Wood_Ashen_A_1x1.webp">Wood Ashen A</option>
            <option value="canvas/doors/small/Door_Wood_Ashen_D_1x1.webp">Wood Ashen D</option>
            <option value="canvas/doors/small/Door_Wood_Ashen_E_1x1.webp">Wood Ashen E</option>
            <option value="canvas/doors/small/Door_Wood_Ashen_L_1x1.webp">Wood Ashen L</option>
            <option value="canvas/doors/small/Door_Wood_Dark_C_1x1.webp">Wood Dark C</option>
            <option value="canvas/doors/small/Door_Wood_Dark_H_1x1.webp">Wood Dark H</option>
            <option value="canvas/doors/small/Door_Wood_Dark_P_1x1.webp">Wood Dark P</option>
            <option value="canvas/doors/small/Door_Wood_Light_B_1x1.webp">Wood Light B</option>
            <option value="canvas/doors/small/Door_Wood_Light_G_1x1.webp">Wood Light G</option>
            <option value="canvas/doors/small/Door_Wood_Light_I_1x1.webp">Wood Light I</option>
            <option value="canvas/doors/small/Door_Wood_Red_D_1x1.webp">Wood Red D</option>
            <option value="canvas/doors/small/Door_Wood_Red_J_1x1.webp">Wood Red J</option>
            <option value="canvas/doors/small/Door_Wood_Red_K2_1x1.webp">Wood Red K2</option>
            <option value="canvas/doors/small/Door_Wood_Walnut_F_1x1.webp">Wood Walnut F</option>
            <option value="canvas/doors/small/Door_Wood_Walnut_H_1x1.webp">Wood Walnut H</option>
            <option value="canvas/doors/small/Door_Wood_Walnut_R_1x1.webp">Wood Walnut R</option>
          </select>
          <img class="da-door-preview" src="" alt="" hidden />
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="hint">Applied to all doors (wall type "Door") using a swing animation. Select "None" to leave doors untextured.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="da-field-card">
      <div class="form-group da-inline-group">
        <label>Door Sound</label>
        <div class="form-fields da-door-row">
          <select name="doorSound">
            <option value="">None</option>
            <option value="futuristicFast">Futuristic (Fast)</option>
            <option value="futuristicHydraulic">Futuristic (Hydraulic)</option>
            <option value="futuristicForcefield">Futuristic (Forcefield)</option>
            <option value="industrial">Industrial</option>
            <option value="industrialCreaky">Industrial (Creaky)</option>
            <option value="jail">Jail</option>
            <option value="jailCreaky">Jail (Creaky)</option>
            <option value="jailHeavy">Jail (Heavy)</option>
            <option value="magicDoor">Magic Door</option>
            <option value="magicWall">Magic Wall</option>
            <option value="metal">Metal</option>
            <option value="slidingMetal">Sliding Metal</option>
            <option value="slidingMetalHeavy">Sliding Metal (Heavy)</option>
            <option value="slidingModern">Sliding Modern</option>
            <option value="slidingWood">Sliding Wood</option>
            <option value="stoneBasic">Stone (Basic)</option>
            <option value="stoneRocky">Stone (Rocky)</option>
            <option value="stoneSandy">Stone (Sandy)</option>
            <option value="woodBasic">Wood (Basic)</option>
            <option value="woodCreaky">Wood (Creaky)</option>
            <option value="woodHeavy">Wood (Heavy)</option>
          </select>
          <button type="button" data-action="previewSound" aria-label="Preview sound">
            <i class="fas fa-play"></i>
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="hint">Sound played when opening or closing imported doors. Select "None" to use the Foundry default.</p>
    </div>

  </div>

  <div class="da-tab-panel da-tab-panel--hidden" data-tab="levels" role="tabpanel">

    <div class="da-field-card">
      <div class="form-group da-inline-group">
        <label>Floor Height</label>
        <div class="form-fields">
          <input type="number" name="uniformFloorHeight" min="1" step="1" value="10" />
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="hint">Applies uniform height to all levels. To use different heights per level, edit each row in the table below.</p>
    </div>

    <p class="hint">The defaults already stack your floors correctly — you only need to edit a row to fine-tune. Each <strong>Name</strong> is pre-filled from the original filename; hover any column header to see what it does, or a thumbnail for its filename and size.</p>

    <div class="da-levels-controls">
      <label class="da-adv-toggle">
        <input type="checkbox" name="showAdvanced" /> Show advanced columns
      </label>
      <span class="da-info-icon" tabindex="0" title="Advanced columns — most maps don't need these:&#10;• Roof: this level acts as a ceiling, shown only when the floor below is active (roofs, overhangs).&#10;• Start: which floor players see when the scene first opens.&#10;• Visible: keep other floors visible at the same time (open atriums, balconies, mezzanines).">&#9432;</span>
    </div>

    <p class="hint da-levels-placeholder">Select a folder above to see level rows.</p>
    <div class="da-levels-list"></div>

  </div>

  <footer class="sheet-footer flexrow">
    <button type="button" data-action="import">
      <i class="fas fa-file-import"></i> Import
    </button>
  </footer>
</div>
